Fujitsu Australia appoints Neville Roach as CEO . Japan - based electronics , computer and telecommunications giant Fujitsu Ltd said on Monday Neville Roach had been appointed chairman and chief executive officer of its 80 percent owned Fujitsu Australia . Roach is currently managing director of the Australian unit . The U . K . - based International Computers holds the other 20 percent of Fujitsu Australia . Other new directors appointed are Naoyuki Akikusa and Atsuyuki Kodama from Fujitsu Ltd , Bryan Daniels , Fujitsu Australia ' s executive director of information systems and Doug Dent , managing director of FBA Computer Technology Services . - - Sydney Newsroom 61 - 2 9373 - 1800 
